{
  "title": "Morsels in 5 minutes",
  "_content": {
    "title": "An introduction to Morsels",
    "description": "Come in. Take your shoes off."
  },
  "_chapters": [
    {
      "title": "Introduction",
      "_stacks": [
        {
          "title": "About the framework",
          "_cards": [
            {
              "_card": "title",
              "_classes": "inverted",
              "_content": {
                "title": "Morsels",
                "subtitle": "A new responsive elearning framework",
                "image": {
                  "src": "resources/icons/web.png"
                },
                "body": "<p><i class=\"material-icons\">access_time</i> 2 minutes</p>",
                "footer": "Swipe this card away to get started&hellip;"
              }
            },
            {
              "_card": "text",
              "_content": {
                "title": "Morsels in a nutshell",
                "body": "<ul><li>Responsive HTML5 framework</li><li>Touch-first methodologies</li><li>PWA (Progressive Web App)</li><li>Lightweight (fast)</li><li>SCORM compliant</li><li>Offline support (Chrome only)</li><li>Quick to build new interactions</li></ul>"
              }
            },
            {
              "_card": "text",
              "_content": {
                "title": "Morsels vs. Adapt",
                "body": "<p>Morsels is not designed as a replacement for Adapt.</p><p>In fact, it is designed to work in parallel with Adapt as a takeaway and support tool.</p><p>Adapt is still better if you need:</p><ul><li>IE8&ndash;10 support</li><li>Full accessibility</li><li>Larger images and videos</li><li>More &quot;themeable&quot;</li></ul>"
              }
            },
            {
              "_card": "text",
              "_content": {
                "title": "Future roadmap",
                "body": "<ul><li>Offline support for all modern browsers</li><li>Full authoring tool</li><li>Native apps for Android and iOS</li><li>SCORM 1.2 and 2004 support</li></ul>"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "title": "Cards and stacks",
          "_cards": [
            {
              "_card": "text",
              "_content": {
                "image": {
                  "src": "https://4.bp.blogspot.com/-gCE-gBljBOk/Vt0Wc-l-F8I/AAAAAAAABsA/vTJh_lfSx3U/s1600/cover.jpg",
                  "alt": "Morsel cards"
                },
                "title": "Cards",
                "body": "<p>Inspired by Google's Material Design, Morsels uses cards to show short snippets of content.</p><p>This keeps the content brief and relevant. It also makes finding the right content easier.</p>"
              }
            },
            {
              "_card": "text",
              "_content": {
                "title": "Card types",
                "body": "<p>Cards can come in many layouts, such as:</p><ul><li>Title</li><li>Text (and image)</li><li>Video</li><li>MCQ</li><li>&hellip;and many more!</li></ul>"
              }
            },
            {
              "_card": "text",
              "_content": {
                "title": "Activities",
                "body": "<p>Each card can have activities attached to it.</p><p>Activities can be optional or mandatory. If they are mandatory, you must complete them before you can dismiss the card.</p>",
                "instruction": "Complete all the activities by clicking on the blue button and then swipe this card"
              },
              "_activities": {
                "_options": {
                  "_optional": false
                },
                "_items": [
                  {
                    "_type": "mcq",
                    "_content": {
                      "title": "Thoughts",
                      "body": "<p>Do you like the sound of Morsels so far?</p>",
                      "instruction": "Select from the list below"
                    },
                    "_items": [
                      {
                        "title": "Yes",
                        "_shouldBeSelected": true
                      },
                      {
                        "title": "No",
                        "_shouldBeSelected": false
                      }
                    ],
                    "_feedback": {
                      "_correct": {
                        "title": "Well done!",
                        "body": "<p>Nice one</p>"
                      },
                      "_incorrect": {
                        "title": "Incorrect",
                        "body": "<p>It's actually pretty sweet&hellip;</p>",
                        "_notes": [
                          "morsels_info"
                        ]
                      },
                      "_common": {
                        "body": "<p>Morsels is awesome.</p>"
                      }
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "_type": "mcq",
                    "_content": {
                      "title": "Thoughts",
                      "body": "<p>Will you use it for your next project?</p>",
                      "instruction": "Select from the list below"
                    },
                    "_items": [
                      {
                        "title": "Of course!",
                        "_shouldBeSelected": true
                      },
                      {
                        "title": "Maybe not",
                        "_shouldBeSelected": false
                      }
                    ],
                    "_feedback": {
                      "_correct": {
                        "title": "Well done!",
                        "body": "<p>Nice one</p>"
                      },
                      "_incorrect": {
                        "title": "Incorrect",
                        "body": "<p>It's actually pretty sweet&hellip;</p>",
                        "_notes": [
                          "morsels_info"
                        ]
                      },
                      "_common": {
                        "body": "<p>Morsels is awesome.</p>"
                      }
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "_card": "text",
              "_content": {
                "image": {
                  "src": "https://camo.envatousercontent.com/40365fec24858cdbdb7ddae12a889c09c2155bbf/687474703a2f2f692e696d6775722e636f6d2f4c754157334b542e6a7067"
                },
                "title": "Stacks",
                "body": "<p>Cards are arranged in a stack - just like cards in real life.</p><p>Once you dismiss the last card in the stack, it is complete and you will move on to the next stack.</p>"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "title": "Components",
          "_cards": [
            {
              "_card": "text",
              "_content": {
                "image": {
                  "src": "https://imageog.flaticon.com/icons/png/512/9/9915.png?size=1200x630f&pad=10,10,10,10&ext=png&bg=FFFFFFFF"
                },
                "title": "Components",
                "body": "<p>Cards can be restrictive.</p><p>To get around this, you can use a component in place of a stack of cards.</p><p>The next example is a conversation component.</p>"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "title": "Conversation example",
          "_component": "conversation",
          "_items": [
            {
              "body": "<p>Do you want to get together or something?</p>"
            },
            {
              "name": "Sarah",
              "body": "<p>How about going to see a movie? Cinemax 26 on Carson Boulevard is showing Enchanted.</p>"
            },
            {
              "name": "Laurie",
              "body": "<p>That sounds like a good idea. Maybe we should go out to eat beforehand.</p>"
            },
            {
              "name": "Sarah",
              "body": "<p>It is fine with me. Where do you want to meet?</p>"
            },
            {
              "body": "<p>Let’s meet at Summer Pizza House. I have not gone there for a long time.</p>"
            },
            {
              "name": "Laurie",
              "body": "<p>Good idea again. I heard they just came up with a new pizza. It should be good because Summer Pizza House always has the best pizza in town.</p>"
            },
            {
              "name": "Sarah",
              "body": "<p>When should we meet?</p>"
            },
            {
              "name": "Christie",
              "body": "<p>Well, the movie is shown at 2:00PM, 4:00PM, 6:00PM and 8:00PM.</p>"
            },
            {
              "name": "Laurie",
              "body": "<p>Why don’t we go to the 2:00PM show? We can meet at Summer Pizza House at noon. That will give us plenty of time to enjoy our pizza.</p>"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "title": "Chapters",
          "_cards": [
            {
              "_card": "text",
              "_content": {
                "title": "Chapters",
                "body": "<p>The stacks of cards and components can be grouped into chapters.</p><p>This is the last card in the chapter.</p><p>Once you dismiss it, you will be taken to the next chapter.</p>"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Formula 1",
      "_content": {
